Part 1: Global Media Keys (Control while minimized)
We need the app to listen for the dedicated "Play/Pause" keys on your keyboard even when the window is in the background. We will use the pynput library, which is safer and less likely to trigger antivirus software than the keyboard library.

Prompt 1: The Media Key Listener

Copy and paste this:

"I need to implement Global Media Keys support.

1. Install Dependency:

I will install pynput (pip install pynput).

2. Create the Manager (media_keys.py):

Create a class MediaKeyHandler that accepts my player instance.

Use pynput.keyboard.Listener to listen for specific keys globally.

Map these keys:

Key.media_play_pause → player.toggle_play()

Key.media_next → player.play_next()

Key.media_previous → player.play_previous()

Thread Safety: Since this runs in a separate thread, ensure the player commands are triggered safely (using app.after or directly if your player is thread-safe).

Add a start() and stop() method to control the listener.

3. Integration:

In main.py, initialize this handler right after the player is created.

Start it on app launch and stop it on app close."

Part 2: Discord Rich Presence (The "Flex" Feature)
This connects your app to Discord so it shows "Listening to Cyberpunk Synthwave" on your profile. You will use pypresence.

